premise_source_doc_sentence: In Norse mythology , from which stems most of the information about the god , Odin is associated with healing , death , royalty , the gallows , knowledge , battle , sorcery , poetry , frenzy , and the runic alphabet , and is the husband of the goddess Frigg .

In Norse mythology , Thor  (  -LSB- θɔr -RSB- from Old Norse Þórr  )  is a hammer-wielding god associated with thunder , lightning , storms , oak trees , strength , the protection of mankind , and also hallowing and fertility .
In Norse mythology , Billingr  (  or Billing  )  is the father of a maiden  (  whose name is not provided  )  desired by Odin .
